The paper deals with network embedding in heterogeneous information networks, which involves machine learning techniques for analyzing complex data structures. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category, as the paper deals with network analysis and embedding. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category, as the paper proposes a new embedding learning algorithm. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category, as the paper deals with semantic relations between nodes in a network. 

cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category, as the paper deals with data structures and relationships between nodes. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category, as the paper deals with machine learning techniques for analyzing complex data structures.
